76561198059760652,Not Recommended,257830,9400272,"Posted: 9 March, 2014",all,j.r.dutka,"So, this game is pretty and that's about it.Without a narrative, you have no idea what it is you're doing and why you're doing it.You are doing puzzles that are almost completely random so you're just doing trial and error until it works and half the time I didn't even understand WHY it worked.  It was just a thing that I did.  Difficulty pays off when things become clear, but this is just ""pull this until a thing happens.""  The puzzles are only difficult by virtue of the fact that they make little sense.  Also, your telekinetic ability is incredibly selective; you can effect something a screen away, but you can't use it to pick something up that's just out of physical reach?Music is pretty boring, the gibberish that passes as speech is very grating on my ears and the sound in general made no impact whatsoever on me.It was a waste of $9.99 and I regret the purchase wholeheartedly."
