,Recommended,257830,12918313,"Posted: 12 November, 2014",all,V snuffles,"I really enjoyed this, a great puzzle game. Some of the puzzles are genuinely challenging to figure out, so that was fun. There was only one puzzle annoying enough for me to look up, the rest were challenging at times but fun to figure out.I really liked the bizarre setting, it has a really nice mood, and the music is *amazing* and fits the setting really well. I also like that the NPCs are really just going about their own business and their lives don't revolve around you as a nice departure from the 'do this for me' quests usually found in point-and-clicks. Achievements ranged from easy to challenging but were fun to fulfill for the most part. The orbs are a little annoying to get sometimes so you might want to guide it once you've had a good go. It would be nice if you got some hints about the remaining orbs once you'd beaten the game or something since they already have hints for the main game and it's less spoilery than looking up a guide that tells you outright where they are.The boss fight feels a bit odd, standing out from the rest of the game mechanics-wise, but it gives meaning to collecting all those orbs which is more than a lot of other games bother to do. And it's not too hard once you get the hang of it. A practise room with a dummy would've been cool though, so you can have used the skills before fighting the big bad.Update: The free update was pretty good as far as I can tell: the new areas had fun, well thought-out puzzles. They fit in seamlessly and apparently there are other improvements which I didn't encounter when I replayed the game. (Possibly they were hints.) It was pretty decent of them to add free bonus content, improve graphics and more fixes to the game."
76561198079145742,Recommended,257830,9241444,"Posted: 23 February, 2014",all,Wurzelzweig [Linux],"Violett is a little girl tumbling into a fantastic adventure where she shrinked to the size of a bug. While the main aim is to find back home to her parent's house, she needs to solve lots of puzzles with many crosslinks. The graphics are nice and cute, the music is interesting like some film score.  She can only walk - in the beginning. Through her journey, she will find many balls/orbs in three different colors and three special glowing orbs that gives her special powers (jump, psychokineses and defense shield). The normal balls will fill the energy levels for all three powers.She has to go to the same scenes several times to completely solve all puzzles and many orbs are hidden very well (sometimes they are invisible hidden). If you are stuck, you can get help with the icon circle in the lower right. If she speaks with animals, you only here some strange queeks with some words and speech bubbles explaining the required item in sketches.The very first scene, where she is trapped in a cage, can only be played once - all other scenes can be visited again. There is an autosave feature but you might want to save your game already right in this first scene (in case you want to get all achievements by finding all orbs). You can also save your current game in new save slots, if you like. Unfortunately, the game ""froze"" a few times, i.e. Violett wasn't able to move anymore, everything else continued on the screen. But saving and restarting solved these issues.<SPOILER ON>The very last scene is some kind of boss fight with the spider queen but I wasn't able to move Violett as I liked to. I somehow made it but this was just try and error and some luck. Too bad as an end for this nice puzzle adventure.</SPOILER OFF>Despite the few glitches, I recommend this time waster as it is challenging and has nice graphics, music and puzzles."
